<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-body">
    <h1 class="title is-3 has-text-danger">Project Overview</h1>
    <p>
      This project utilizes data sourced from the
      <a href="http://makeup-api.herokuapp.com/"><strong>Makeup API</strong></a>
      database, providing users access to a diverse catalog of over 800 makeup
      products. The application allows users to explore and navigate through
      these products, sorting them by brand and category for easy discovery.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="content">
  <h1 class="title is-4">Database Structure</h1>

  <div class="box">
    <h2 class="subtitle is-6">makeup_products Table:</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>id</strong> (Integer, primary key): Unique identifier for each
        product.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>product_name</strong> (String): Name of the makeup product.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>product_category_id</strong> (Integer, foreign key referencing
        <code>product_categories</code>): Identifies the product's category.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>product_tags</strong> (String): Tags associated with the
        product.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>brand_id</strong> (Integer, foreign key referencing
        <code>brands</code>): Identifies the product's brand.
      </li>
      <li><strong>price</strong> (Decimal): Price of the product.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>description</strong> (Text): Detailed description of the
        product.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>tag_list</strong> (String): Additional tags or metadata related
        to the product.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>api_featured_image</strong> (String): URL or path to the
        featured image of the product.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <h2 class="subtitle is-6">product_categories Table:</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>id</strong> (Integer, primary key): Unique identifier for each
        category.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>product_type</strong> (String): Type of the product (e.g.,
        Blush, Lipstick).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>product_category</strong> (String): Specific category within the
        product type (e.g., Matte, Glossy).
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <h2 class="subtitle is-6">brands Table:</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>id</strong> (Integer, primary key): Unique identifier for each
        brand.
      </li>
      <li><strong>brand_name</strong> (String): Name of the brand.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h1 class="title is-4">Data Integration and Relationships:</h1>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>makeup_products</strong> references
      <code>product_categories</code> through the
      <strong>product_category_id</strong> column and
      <code>brands</code> through the <strong>brand_id</strong> column.
    </li>
    <li>
      Each product in <strong>makeup_products</strong> is associated with a
      specific product category and brand, ensuring accurate categorization and
      consistent brand referencing.
    </li>
    <li>
      The <code>product_categories</code> table maintains unique combinations of
      <strong>product_type</strong> and <strong>product_category</strong>,
      facilitating efficient querying and filtering based on various product
      attributes.
    </li>
    <li>
      The <code>brands</code> table ensures that brand names are consistently
      referenced across products, enhancing data integrity and usability.
    </li>
  </ul>

